    {
      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "Many complaints have been received\nfrom shippers along the Central Wash\nington line who claim goods shipped\nby them over the new Adrian cutoff\nwhich connects the Central Washing\nton with the Great Northern, do not\nreach their destination in anything like\na reasonable time. As an instance OF\nthis. one load of -four shipped three\nweeks ago has not yet reached the\ncoast. The Great Northern officials\nwill look into the matter with view\nto remedying the trouble."
    }
